    <!--
        Encouragement — process-praise from growth-mindset research (Mueller &amp; Dweck 1998, Gunderson 2013).
        Names strategy, effort, improvement — not intelligence or talent. Misses reframed as "the brain growing" (Moser 2011).
    -->
    <string-array name="praise_correct">
        <item>You followed the steps carefully — and it worked!</item>
        <item>You used what you learned right here. Your connecting power is growing!</item>
        <item>I can tell you read the whole problem before solving. Great habit.</item>
        <item>You solved it your own way! Want to explain how you did it?</item>
        <item>Your skill is growing with practice. One step ahead of yesterday\'s you!</item>
    </string-array>
    <string-array name="praise_wrong">
        <item>A miss means your brain is hard at work growing right now!</item>
        <item>So close! Let\'s find where it got tangled — finding it makes it real skill.</item>
        <item>You just haven\'t solved this \'yet\'. That \'yet\' matters!</item>
        <item>Want to try it a different way? Switching methods is a skill too.</item>
        <item>Taking on a hard problem is awesome. Only easy ones won\'t help you grow.</item>
    </string-array>
    <string-array name="praise_streak">
        <item>Streak! Your method is getting sturdier and sturdier.</item>
        <item>Looks like this got easy for you — let\'s try something harder!</item>
        <item>Streak going strong! The steady practice is showing.</item>
    </string-array>
    <string-array name="praise_stuck">
        <item>You\'ve hit the tricky part — this is the hardest stretch. Read the solution and try just one more.</item>
        <item>This is plenty for today. It\'ll look clearer when you come back tomorrow.</item>
        <item>You know more now than a moment ago. Retrace the basics and it\'ll click soon.</item>
    </string-array>

